		/// Core Audio only. Desktop only. When enabled, allows the sample rate of the device to be changed at the operating system level. This<br/>
		/// is disabled by default in order to prevent intrusive changes to the user's system. This is useful if you want to use a sample rate<br/>
		/// that is known to be natively supported by the hardware thereby avoiding the cost of resampling. When set to true, miniaudio will<br/>
